I see the issue! The SAFE_IDLE case has this logic:
```c
else {
    /* Both sensors valid, level sufficient, but turbidity already clear - go to complete */
    set_complete(controller);
}
```

This goes to COMPLETE if we have both sensors valid, level >= 40, but turbidity <= 35. But this doesn't make sense when we're in SAFE_IDLE due to timeout! We should stay in SAFE_IDLE until sensors are fresh again.

The fix is to only go to COMPLETE when we're in SAFE_IDLE and the level is below the threshold, not when turbidity is clear. Let me fix this:

